      <bridgehead>Tasks</bridgehead>
      <formalpara>
        <title>Ensure ODBC to JDBC Bridge Primary Keys (PKs) are not nullable</title>
        <para>The Visual Studio 2008 Entity Data Model (EDM) requires that all primary keys are
<emphasis>NOT</emphasis>

   Nullable, and will fail to generate an EDM if any are. Thus ensure any tables to
be used are defined as not nullable in the ODBC to JDBC Bridge database schema before attempting to generate
an EDM. In the case of the ODBC to JDBC Bridge Virtuoso Northwind Demo database all tables are not
nullable, thus this should not be an issue in this case.
    </para>
      </formalpara>
